{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":9267,"record_hash":"sha256:576da08988db2baf32dd594a6f68f13e929a5ad3dd3a48391d5a9edf6ec5719a","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:01:51.447Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"Found 3 worthwhile things. No scary stuff.\\n\\n1. **CLI target normalization is in the wrong layer**\\n   [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:307) owns `associated_session_target_key()`, but the public primitive is `find_related_sessions(repo, RelatedTarget::Branch(...))` in [read.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta/read.rs:232). That means future callers can easily pass `\\\"main\\\"` and get no results unless they copy CLI normalization.\\n\\n   Minimal fix: move the normalization beside `RelatedTarget`, maybe as small constructors:\\n   `RelatedTarget::branch(value)`, `RelatedTarget::review(value)`, `RelatedTarget::change(value)`.\\n   Then CLI just calls those. This keeps the primitive reliable, not CLI-special.\\n\\n2. **`CommandOutput` is becoming a nullable bag**\\n   [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:47) now has `message`, optional `target_kind`, optional `target_key`, optional `sessions`. For `associated-sessions`, JSON includes an empty `message`, which is a smell.\\n\\n   Minimal fix: make it an internal enum:\\n   `CommandOutput::Message { message }`\\n   `CommandOutput::AssociatedSessions { target_kind, target_key, sessions }`\\n\\n   That gives clean serde shape and simpler display matching. No public API cost since it’s private.\\n\\n3. **`AssociatedSessionTarget` is awkwardly public-but-not-exported**\\n   [cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:104) is `pub` because public `Command` exposes it, but [lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/lib.rs:11) does not re-export it. So the public `Command::AssociatedSessions` variant leaks a type that external callers can’t conveniently name.\\n\\n   Minimal fix: either re-export it from `lib.rs`, or better, if we do item 1, rename it to a CLI-only `TargetKind` and re-export it only if needed. Since `Command` is already public for `but`, I’d re-export the type if it remains in the variant.\\n\\nTiny non-issue: the clones/ownership look fine. `target_key: String` and `Vec<RelatedSession>` are owned because the command output owns them; `join(\\\",\\\")` is display-only and harmless.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:01:51.447Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}